Are you wondering what to gift your loved ones this Christmas but also want to keep it personalised and easy to make? Look no more and make this gorgeous Sticky Orange Dates Pudding directly in @freshwrapp 

Not only does the food feel fresh long after cooking but Freshwrapp aluminium foils and containers are up to 70% thicker, sturdy & strong. It’s OTG safe and meets up to all the standards of the Indian bureau! It’s an efficient product for everyday cooking as well as commercial purposes

Sticky Orange Toffee Dates Pudding 

For the Pudding 

1/2 cup Dates , pitted and roughly chopped
175ml Milk
1/2 teaspoon Baking soda
100gms Brown Sugar 
1/2 teaspoon Cinnamon Powder 
1 WholeOrange Rind 
1/4 teaspoon Salt
95 gms All Purpose Flour (Maida)
115gms Butter (Unsalted)

For Orange Toffee Sauce 
200gms Brown Sugar )
55gms Butter (Salted) 
220ml Fresh cream
1 teaspoon Vanilla Extract 
Half an orange juice 

Garnish 
Candied Orange 
Chopped Dates 

Cook the dates in milk and add cinnamon powder, Orange rind, salt and baking soda to it. Baking soda will break down and cook the dates. Keep this mixture aside and let it cook for a bit. In a bowl, cream the brown sugar and butter. To this add the prepared dates mixture and Flour. Mix this batter well but be sure to not over mix it. Add this to the Freshwrapp container and bake it directly in the oven at 170• for 15-20 minutes. 
While this is baking, prepare the toffee sauce. Add all the ingredients together in a pan and cook it in medium flame till the sugar and butter all mix and melt well. For the Candied orange, take the Freshwrapp Aluminium Foil and add thinly sliced orange, sprinkle it with little brown sugar, wrap it fully and bake it for 10-15 minutes in the oven. Your amazing cake is now ready 😍

Shot & Edited @danushbhaskar

SHUT UP PANNADHINGA
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Hi guys! Today is the final day of the global ‘16 Days of Activism Against Gender-Based Violence’, and I have a special message for you - Shut Up Pannadhinga. 

In partnership with @pcvc_2000, @usconsulatechennai and @thenewsminute I bring to you this video, as a reminder to every woman that if we are facing violence at home, we must not stay silent, and seek help. 

And here is a personal message from me - 

DONOT put up with such violence and let you or anyone else you know to go through with it ! You ALWAYS have a choice to walk out and there will always be help ! This pandemic saw an increase in such domestic violence and this has to STOP. No one is less , no one is more ! 

Share this video widely, and if you or someone you know is facing violence at home, call the national domestic violence hotline, Dhwani at 1800 102 7282. #ShutUpPannadhinga

Homemade Lemon Tea ! 🍋🍋

As simple as it sounds, most people make a rookie mistake while making this which is - Adding too much tea powder! 😬

For every 500ml of water use just quarter tsp of tea leaf or powder ! 

For every 500ml add juice of 2- 2.5whole lemon depending on the tanginess of it. Add sweetener if your choice either sugar or honey or can have it even without any sweetener. Garnish with mint leaves and enjoy ! 🥰

To elevate it further , add pounded ginger while boiling the water. Can also add Karpooravali (Ajwain) leaves too ! Perfect for this weather and for lactose intolerant people! 🌼

Go run, make this now and let me know how it was ! 🫶🏼🍋

How many Lemon Tea fans here ???
